self.title: CDISC SEND Expected Onset of Rad/Nuc Targeted Injury Response Terminology

definition: Terminology related to the relative timing of the expected onset of the targeted injury, with respect to rad/nuc challenge agent exposure.
name: Expected Onset of Rad/Nuc Targeted Injury Response
preferredTerm: CDISC SEND Expected Onset of Rad/Nuc Targeted Injury Response Terminology
synonyms: Expected Onset of Rad/Nuc Targeted Injury Response

terms.definition: The manifestation of the injury, disease, or condition is characterized as having both acute and delayed onsets.
The manifestation of the injury, disease, or condition is characterized as having an immediate or early onset.
The manifestation of the injury, disease, or condition is characterized as having a delayed onset.
